==Korean==
===Adjective===
'''푸르다''' (''pureuda'')
# To be '''[[blue]]''' (''probably cognate with Old English '''[[ bœl]]''', Dutch '''[[vuur]]''', Greek [[πῦρ]] ('''pyr''') "'''[[fire]]'''"'') cf. '''[[pure]]''' , Dutch '''[[puur]]''', Latin '''[[purus]]'''
# To be [[green]]
# To be '''[[fresh]]'''  

====Synonyms====
*[[파랗다]] (''parahda'') To be [[blue]]; [[green]]
*[[청]] ([[靑]], ''cheong'') [[blue]]; [[green]]
*[[녹]] ([[綠]], ''nog, nok; rog, rok'') [[green]]; '''[[rust]]''' (''cognate with'' [[red]], German [[Rost]], French [[rouille]], Italian [[ruggine]])

====Derived terms====
*[[검]]푸르다 (''geom-'') To be [[black and blue]]
*[[푸르스름]]하다 (''pureuseureum-hada'') To be [[bluish]]; [[greenish]] 
*[[푸릇푸릇]]하다 (''pureus-pureus-hada, pureut-pureut-'') To be [[bluish]] (''here and there'') cf. [[purple]] from Old English '''[[purpure]]''' : <span style="background:purple">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; </span>
*[[푸성귀]] (''puseonggwi'') [[greens]], [[vegetables]]
*[[풋]] (''pus, put'') (''prefix'') '''[[green]]''', [[fresh]], [[unripe]], [[inexperienced]]
*[[풋나기]] (''pusnagi, put-'') [[inexperienced]] [[person]], [[amateur]], [[beginner]], [[novice]]
*[[풋내]] (''pusnae, put-'') [[smell]] of [[greens]] (''especially'', [[unripe]]) (''synonym to'' [[비린내]] (''birinnae'') cf. Latin '''[[viridis]]''' "[[green]]")

